).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3216DCF0C7CFFC2FF0453C1FAC48220" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B843E440C7CFFC2FF0453C1FAC48220" blockId="5.[151,1437,1440,2005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FF0453C1FED183B5" bold="true" box="[197,292,1764,1789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FEED53C3FE3D83B5" box="[300,456,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Megabeleses" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnoliae">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FEED53C3FE3D83B5" box="[300,456,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. magnoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeds on leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FD6553C3FC8383B4" authority="Desr." authorityName="Desr." box="[676,886,1765,1789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="denudata">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FD6553C3FCC683B5" box="[676,819,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. denudata</emphasis>
Desr.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FC6C53C3FBDD83B5" box="[941,1064,1765,1789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="liliflora">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FC6C53C3FBDD83B5" box="[941,1064,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. liliflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Mt. Dabieshan above alt. 
<specimenCount id="9D3DF5CD0C7CFFC2FAB353C1FF418268" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CC393A10C7CFFC2FAB353C1FF458268" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
One generation occurs per year. Adults have been found from mid March to the end of April. Larvae aggregate on leaves and damage the plants from the end of April to the beginning of June, and overwinter below a tree as prepupae in soil at depths of up to 
<quantity id="4CC393A10C7CFFC2FE375275FDCA8220" box="[502,575,1872,1896]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
. See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA43B50C7CFFC2FDB85275FC9B8220" author="Ding" box="[633,878,1872,1896]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" refString="Ding, Y. Z. &amp; Zheng, H. S. (1999) Study on the sawfly Megabeleses crassitarsis (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae, Allantinae). Scientia Silvae Sinicae, 35 (5), 68 - 71." type="journal article" year="1999">
Ding &amp; Zheng (
<number id="3DF32C630C7CFFC2FCEA5275FC908220" box="[811,869,1872,1896]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for details of the biology of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3216DCF0C7CFFC2FF045250FE7A829C" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B843E440C7CFFC2FF045250FE7A829C" blockId="5.[151,1437,1440,2005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FF045250FECC82C5" bold="true" box="[197,313,1909,1933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA43B50C7CFFC2FE855251FDB182C4" author="Ding" box="[324,580,1908,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" refString="Ding, Y. Z. &amp; Zheng, H. S. (1999) Study on the sawfly Megabeleses crassitarsis (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae, Allantinae). Scientia Silvae Sinicae, 35 (5), 68 - 71." type="journal article" year="1999">
Ding &amp; Zheng (
<number id="3DF32C630C7CFFC2FDC35251FDC982C4" box="[514,572,1908,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the present species under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FB9A5253FAF082C5" box="[1115,1285,1910,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Megabeleses" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassitarsis">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FB9A5253FAF082C5" box="[1115,1285,1910,1933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. crassitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7ED40C7CFFC2FA935251FA6C82C4" box="[1362,1433,1908,1932]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">China</collectingCountry>
. Actually, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FEC552BCFE5F82F8" box="[260,426,1945,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Megabeleses" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassitarsis">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FEC552BCFE5F82F8" box="[260,426,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. crassitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7ED40C7CFFC2FD9952BCFD6E82F8" box="[600,667,1945,1968]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FD1452BCFC8982F8" box="[725,892,1945,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Megabeleses" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassitarsis">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FD1452BCFC8982F8" box="[725,892,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. crassitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7ED40C7CFFC2FC3F52BDFBB482F8" box="[1022,1089,1944,1968]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">China</collectingCountry>
is a separate species described here as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B45C70C7CFFC2FF2D529BFE7D829D" box="[236,392,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Megabeleses" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnoliae">
<emphasis id="B94FE2560C7CFFC2FF2D529BFE7D829D" box="[236,392,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="41">M. magnoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
